text:
72-70 Willett Street, at and adjoining the S.E. corner of Rivington Street. No. 70 is the Beth Hanerdrash Hagodol Synagogue.

June 17, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.

Willett Street, east side, north from a point (No. 82 on right margin) slightly to the north of Rivington Street, to Hamilton Fish Park, showing a synagogue standing between two demolitions which bore No's 88 and 92-94. The low structure at the left is in the aforementioned park and the writer believes same to be the new swimming pool.

June 29 1938.

P.L. Sperr

86 Willett Street, east side, between Rivington and Stanton Streets, showing a rear view of the enumerated tenement and a two story frame shack behind same and on the same plot of ground. The photographer is viewing same in a north westward direction from the adjacent clearance that extends thru the block from Sheriff to Willett Streets.

June 29, 1938.

P.L. Sperr
